---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Best Action & 360 Camera (2026) ‚Äî cameraupick" description="Capture everything. The best action cameras and 360 cameras for sports, travel, and creative reframing from GoPro, Insta360, and DJI.">
<main class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h1>Best Action & 360 Camera (2026)</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">
            Shoot first, frame later. Modern 360 cameras capture every angle at once, so you never miss a moment. Action
            cams are tougher, sharper, and steadier than ever.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-media">
          <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/action-360.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/action-360.webp?v=20260111" alt="Action camera mounted on helmet"
            loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1400" height="900"
            style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;">
</picture>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>At a Glance: Top 3 Picks</h2>
      <div class="comparison-table-wrapper">
        <table class="comparison">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Model</th>
              <th>Type</th>
              <th>Resolution</th>
              <th>Waterproof</th>
              <th>Price</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="#insta360-x4" class="product-name">Insta360 X4</a>
              </td>
              <td><span class="tag">360 / Creative</span></td>
              <td>8K 360</td>
              <td>10m</td>
              <td class="price-check">Check Price</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="#gopro-13" class="product-name">GoPro Hero 13</a>
              </td>
              <td><span class="tag">POV Video</span></td>
              <td>5.3K</td>
              <td>10m</td>
              <td class="price-check">Check Price</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="#dji-action-5" class="product-name">DJI Action 5 Pro</a>
              </td>
              <td><span class="tag">Low Light</span></td>
              <td>4K 120p</td>
              <td>20m</td>
              <td class="price-check">Check Price</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 1 -->
    <section class="section" id="insta360-x4">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">‚ú® Best 360 Camera</span>
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/insta360-x4.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/insta360-x4.webp" alt="Insta360 X4 Review" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">Insta360 X4</h3>
            <p>
              The X4 solves the biggest problem with 360 video: sharpness. With 8K resolution, when you reframe (crop)
              into a standard 16:9 video, it actually looks crisp and 4K-ish.
            </p>
            <p>
              The "Invisible Selfie Stick" effect is pure magic. It automatically stitches out the stick, making it look
              like a drone is following you 3 feet away. It's the ultimate tool for solo travelers and motorcycle
              riders.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Resolution</span>
                <span class="spec-value">8K 360 Video</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Battery</span>
                <span class="spec-value">135 Minutes</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Reframing</span>
                <span class="spec-value">AI App Driven</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Protection</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Removable Guards</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>8K resolution makes reframed footage usable</li>
              <li>Magic "Third Person View" (Drone Shot)</li>
              <li>Incredible mobile app for easy editing</li>
              <li>Removable lens guards (finally!)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Physically larger/heavier than older models</li>
              <li>Low light performance is still grainy</li>
              <li>Requires a powerful phone/PC to edit 8K</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 2 -->
    <section class="section" id="gopro-13">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">üèÑ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è The King of POV</span>
            <!-- Reusing Hero 13 image from vlog guide -->
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/gopro-hero-13.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/gopro-hero-13.webp" alt="GoPro Hero 13 Review" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">GoPro Hero 13</h3>
            <p>
              For traditional POV (point of view) action‚Äîmountain biking, surfing, skiing‚ÄîGoPro is still the king. The
              chassis is proven tough, and the mounting system (fingers) is universal.
            </p>
            <p>
              The 8:7 aspect ratio sensor is brilliant. It shoots a nearly square image, allowing you to crop a vertical
              video for Instagram and a horizontal video for YouTube from the exact same file.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Resolution</span>
                <span class="spec-value">5.3K 60fps</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Sensor</span>
                <span class="spec-value">8:7 Aspect Ratio</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Stabilization</span>
                <span class="spec-value">HyperSmooth 7.0</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Lens</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Max Lens Mod 2.0</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Industry standard mounting ecosystem</li>
              <li>Square sensor allows vertical+horizontal crop</li>
              <li>GPS telemetry overlays (speed, altitude)</li>
              <li>Compatible with Max Lens Mod for ultra-wide field</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Overheats if static (needs airflow)</li>
              <li>Touch screen can be finicky when wet</li>
              <li>Battery life in cold isn't perfect</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 3 -->
    <section class="section" id="dji-action-5">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">üåô Low Light Champ</span>
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/dji-action-5.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/dji-action-5.webp" alt="DJI Osmo Action 5 Pro Review" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">DJI Osmo Action 5 Pro</h3>
            <p>
              While GoPro owns the daylight, DJI owns the night (and the water). The Action 5 Pro has a larger 1/1.3"
              sensor that gathers way more light, making your evening footage look clean rather than muddy.
            </p>
            <p>
              It's also waterproof down to 20 meters <em>without</em> a case (GoPro is only 10m). The magnetic mounting
              system is faster and less annoying than GoPro's screw mount.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Sensor</span>
                <span class="spec-value">1/1.3" CMOS</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Waterproof</span>
                <span class="spec-value">20m ( Deep)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Battery</span>
                <span class="spec-value">4 Hours (Max)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Mount</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Magnetic Quick</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Best low-light image quality in class</li>
              <li>Deeper waterproofing (20m)</li>
              <li>Magnetic mount is extremely convenient</li>
              <li>Color temperature sensor for accurate underwater color</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Stabilization crops in slightly more than GoPro</li>
              <li>Smaller accessory ecosystem</li>
              <li>Resolution tops out at 4K (GoPro does 5.3K)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>360 vs Action: Which one?</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Get 360 If...</h3>
          <p>You want unique angles (like the drone shot) or if you are terrible at framing your subject. It captures
            everything, so you can't miss.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Get Action If...</h3>
          <p>You want the highest quality video (4K/5.3K sharp) and simplicity. You just hit record and go, no editing
            or reframing required.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

  
    <!-- Author Box -->
    <section class="section author-box" style="background: var(--bg-soft); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; margin-top: 32px;">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start;">
        <img src="/assets/images/team-avatar.webp" alt="cameraupick Editorial Team" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: contain; background: white; border: 2px solid var(--accent); padding: 4px;">
        <div>
          <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">Written by cameraupick Editorial Team</h4>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">
            Our team of professional photographers and videographers has 10+ years of experience testing cameras. 
            We buy our own gear and provide honest, unbiased reviews.
          </p>
          <a href="/about" style="font-size: 14px; margin-top: 8px; display: inline-block;">Learn more about our testing process ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  
    <section class="section" id="affiliate">
      <h2>Partner Note</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        We buy or rent our own equipment. No manufacturer paid for this guide. We earn a commission when you use our
        affiliate links, which keeps this site ad-free.
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
